%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbosses-managers-accidental-managers-no-formal-training-survey-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagement%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%20scheme%2C%20so%20you%20would%20end%20up%20running%20your%20own%20shop%20within%20two%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20crucial%20part%20of%20his%20training%20involved%20passing%20four%20levels%20of%20the%20Wine%20%26amp%3B%20Spirit%20Education%20Trust%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsetglobal.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediploma%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20offers%20a%20range%20of%20qualifications%20in%20various%20alcoholic%20beverages%2C%20from%20beginner%20to%20advanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20these%20formative%20years%2C%20Hemming%20discovered%20a%20passion%20for%20wine%20that%20extended%20beyond%20the%20basic%20training%20he%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20kind%20of%20happened%20by%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20Hemming%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20ended%20up%20learning%20a%20lot%20about%20wine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20curiosity%20drove%20him%20to%20explore%20the%20industry%20further%2C%20leading%20him%20to%20Australia%20in%202008%2C%20where%20he%20gained%20hands-on%20experience%20in%20winemaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20Australia%2C%20Hemming%20found%20a%20way%20to%20combine%20his%20passions%20for%20writing%20and%20wine%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Flife-arts%2Fjancis-robinson%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJancis%20Robinson%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20longtime%20wine%20correspondent%20for%20the%20Financial%20Times%2C%20offered%20him%20a%20writing%20role%2C%20which%20he%20continues%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205c82c44-1ffe-47cf-b3cf-783eff038cf7%5C%22%3EMaster%20of%20wine%20journey%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20WSET%20diploma%2C%20Hemming%20started%20the%20lengthy%20process%20of%20becoming%20a%20master%20of%20wine%20in%202009%2C%20which%20took%20him%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20master%20of%20wine%20qualification%20is%20strictly%20aimed%20at%20professionals%2C%26quot%3B%20Hemming%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecoming%20a%20master%20of%20wine%20involves%20passing%20three%20stages%2C%20including%20a%20series%20of%20theory%20and%20practical%20exams%2C%20and%20completing%20a%20detailed%20research%20paper%20about%20the%20study%20of%20wine.%20For%20Hemming's%20research%20paper%2C%20he%20analyzed%20nearly%2030%2C000%20wine%20books%20published%20over%20100%20years%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20where%20he%20studied%20publishing%20trends%20and%20topics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20can%20cost%20over%2023%2C000%20pounds%2C%20or%20around%20%2430%2C000%2C%20for%20candidates%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20Europe%20and%20over%20%2419%2C000%20for%20North%20American%20candidates%2C%20per%20the%20UK-based%20Institute%20of%20Masters%20of%20Wine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20qualifying%20to%20take%20the%20examinations%20is%20a%20significant%20hurdle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20even%20register%2C%20you%20must%20have%20a%20reference%20from%20your%20employer%20saying%20that%20you%20are%20working%20in%20a%20wine%20role%2C%26quot%3B%20Hemming%20said%2C%20along%20with%20a%20recommendation%20from%20another%20master%20of%20wine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPassing%20the%20master%20of%20wine%20qualification%20is%20another%20barrier%20to%20entry%2C%20with%20fail%20rates%20remaining%20%26quot%3Bunfortunately%20incredibly%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20Hemming%20told%20BI.%20When%20the%20examination%20was%20first%20introduced%20in%201953%2C%20only%2028%25%20of%20candidates%20passed%2C%20according%20to%20the%20institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%2C%20Hemming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jancisrobinson.com%2Farticles%2Fdiary-of-an-mw-student-the-end%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompared%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20title%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BOscars%20of%20the%20wine%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20seven%20decades%20later%2C%20the%20program%20is%20still%20diffic