businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-raising-money-strawberry-after-rough-start-year-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20founded%20OpenAI%20in%202015%20with%20a%20lofty%20mission%3A%20to%20develop%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20that%20%26quot%3Bbenefits%20all%20of%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20chose%20to%20be%20a%20nonprofit%20to%20support%20that%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20company%20gets%20closer%20to%20developing%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%2C%20a%20still%20mostly%20theoretical%20version%20of%20AI%20that%20can%20reason%20as%20well%20as%20humans%2C%20and%20the%20money%20from%20excited%20investors%20pours%20in%2C%20some%20are%20worried%20Altman%20is%20losing%20sight%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bbenefits%20all%20of%20humanity%26quot%3B%20part%20of%20the%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20gradual%20but%20perhaps%20inevitable%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20announced%20in%202019%20that%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-mulls-turning-openai-into-a-regular-company-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadding%20a%20for-profit%20arm%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20help%20fund%20its%20nonprofit%20mission%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20true%20to%20its%20original%20spirit%2C%20the%20company%20would%20limit%20the%20profits%20investors%20could%20take%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20increase%20our%20ability%20to%20raise%20capital%20while%20still%20serving%20our%20mission%2C%20and%20no%20pre-existing%20legal%20structure%20we%20know%20of%20strikes%20the%20right%20balance%2C%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20said%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BOur%20solution%20is%20to%20create%20OpenAI%20LP%20as%20a%20hybrid%20of%20a%20for-profit%20and%20nonprofit%E2%80%94which%20we%20are%20calling%20a%20'capped-profit'%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20deft%20move%20that%2C%20on%20its%20surface%2C%20appeared%20intended%20to%20satisfy%20employees%20and%20stakeholders%20concerned%20about%20developing%20the%20technology%20safely%2C%20and%20those%20who%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20company%20more%20aggressively%20produce%20and%20release%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20investment%20poured%20into%20the%20for-profit%20side%2C%20and%20the%20company's%20notoriety%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-koenigsegg-regera-expensive-sports-car-video-openai-musk-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20Altman's%20notoriety%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20increased%2C%20some%20got%20nervous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20board%20briefly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%23chatgpt-was-made-public-so-openai-could-use-feedback-from-users-to-improve-the-bot-18%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eousted%20Altman%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20concerns%20that%20the%20company%20was%20too%20aggressively%20releasing%20products%20without%20prioritizing%20safety.%20Employees%2C%20and%20most%20notably%20Microsoft%20(with%20its%20multibillion-dollar%20investment)%2C%20came%20to%20Altman's%20rescue.%20Altman%20returned%20to%20his%20position%20after%20just%20a%20few%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cultural%20rift%2C%20however%2C%20had%20been%20exposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20company's%20top%20researchers%20%E2%80%94%20Jan%20Leike%20and%20Ilya%20Sutskever%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjan-leike-ilya-sutskever-resignations-superalignment-openai-superintelligence-safe-humanity-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboth%20soon%20resigned%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20duo%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20company's%20so-called%20superalignment%20team%2C%20which%20was%20tasked%20with%20ensuring%20the%20company%20developed%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20safely%20%E2%80%94%20the%20central%20tenet%20of%20OpenAI's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20then%20dissolved%20the%20superalignment%20team%20in%20its%20entirety%20later%20that%20same%20month.%20After%20leaving%2C%20Leike%20said%20on%20X%20that%20the%20team%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bsailing%20against%20the%20wind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20must%20become%20a%20safety-first%20AGI%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Leike%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20adding%20that%20building%20generative%20AI%20is%20%26quot%3Ban%20inherently%20dangerous%20endeavor%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20now%20more%20concerned%20with%20building%20%26quot%3Bshiny%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20now%20that%20OpenAI%20has%20nearly%20completed%20its%20transformation%20into%20a%20Big%20Tech-stye%20%26quot%3Bmove%20fast%20and%20break%20things%26quot%3B%20behemoth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFortune%20reported%20that%20Altman%20told%20employees%20in%20a%20meeting%20last%20week%20that%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20move%20away%20from%20nonprofit%20board%20control%2C%20which%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Boutgrown%2C%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReuters%20reported%20on%20Saturday%20that%20OpenAI%20is%20now%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20securing%20another%20%246.5%20billion%20in%20investment%2C%20which%20would%20value%20the%20company%20at%20%24150%20billion.%20But%20sources%20told%20Reuters%20that%20the%20investment%20comes%20with%20a%20catch%3A%20OpenAI%20must%20abandon%20its%20profit%20cap%20on%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20place%20OpenAI%20ideologically%20distant%20from%20its%20dreamy%20early%20days%2C%20when%20its%20technology%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20open%20source%20and%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20it%20remains%20focused%20on%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20AI%20that%20benefits%20everyone%26quot%3B%20while%20continuing%20to%20work%20with%20its%20nonprofit%20board.%20%26quot%3BThe%20nonprofit%20is%20core%20to%20our%20mission%20and%20will%20continue